<emphasis id="B939EA94FFB0FFB0FF1216CDC6B948FE" bold="true" box="[151,470,1425,1450]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" reason="1">Type specimens examined.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="54F68824FFB0FFB0FE6D16CEC53748FE" box="[488,600,1426,1450]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Lectotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount id="9D4BFD0FFFB0FFB0FDE716CEC51848FD" box="[610,631,1426,1449]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
, (here designated) (
<collectionCode id="ED5CAE43FFB0FFB0FCDC16CDC4C048FD" box="[857,943,1425,1449]" country="Australia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34982" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34982" name="South Australia Museum" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="Museum">SAMA</collectionCode>
), Cue, W.A. H.W. Brown, Co-Type H.J.C., 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D05FFB0FFB0FF1216E9C52F4899" authority="Carter Id." authorityName="Carter Id." box="[151,576,1461,1485]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="septem-plagiata">
<emphasis id="B939EA94FFB0FFB0FF1216E9C6A74899" box="[151,456,1461,1485]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Melobasis septem-plagiata</emphasis>
Carter Id.
</taxonomicName>
by H.J. Carter, 
<typeStatus id="54F68824FFB0FFB0FD7E16E9C4F14899" box="[763,926,1461,1485]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D05FFB0FFB0FC2916E9C2F3489A" authority="Carter, B. Levey" authorityName="Carter, B. Levey" box="[940,1436,1461,1486]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="septemplagiata">
<emphasis id="B939EA94FFB0FFB0FC2916E9C3BC4899" box="[940,1235,1461,1485]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Melobasis septemplagiata</emphasis>
Carter, B. Levey
</taxonomicName>
det. 
<typeStatus id="54F68824FFB0FFB0FF491685C60B48A5" box="[204,356,1497,1521]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Paralectotype</typeStatus>
<specimenCount id="9D4BFD0FFFB0FFB0FEF41686C6E948A5" box="[369,390,1498,1521]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
(
<collectionCode id="ED5CAE43FFB0FFB0FE1F1685C69E48A5" box="[410,497,1497,1521]" country="Australia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34982" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34982" name="South Australia Museum" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="Museum">SAMA</collectionCode>
), mounted to left of 
<typeStatus id="54F68824FFB0FFB0FD6B1686C43148A6" box="[750,862,1498,1522]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Lectotype</typeStatus>
on same card. Carter in his original description mentions 
<specimenCount id="9D4BFD0FFFB0FFB0FE8D16A1C6D04B41" box="[264,447,1533,1557]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="generic">eight specimens</specimenCount>
from Cue, and says the types are in the Australian Museum. I have only found 
<specimenCount id="9D4BFD0FFFB0FFB0FAE816A1C6634B6D" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="generic">four specimens</specimenCount>
from Cue and have therefore based my 
<typeStatus id="54F68824FFB0FFB0FD49157EC4534B6E" box="[716,828,1570,1594]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Lectotype</typeStatus>
designation on the two labelled cotype. The other 
<specimenCount id="9D4BFD0FFFB0FFB0FAF7157EC6634B09" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
from Cue in (
<collectionCode id="ED5CAE43FFB0FFB0FE2B1519C5644B09" box="[430,523,1605,1629]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">WAMA</collectionCode>
) are without original determination labels and these are not conspecific with the 
<typeStatus id="54F68824FFB0FFB0FF121536C6684BD6" box="[151,263,1642,1666]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">Lectotype</typeStatus>
designated above but are specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D05FFB0FFB0FD501536C43E4BD5" authority="Levey, 2012" authorityName="Levey" authorityYear="2012" box="[725,849,1641,1665]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brittoni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B939EA94FFB0FFB0FD501536C43E4BD5" box="[725,849,1641,1665]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">M. brittoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B939EA94FFB0FFB0FCDF1535C4F34BD5" bold="true" box="[858,924,1641,1665]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20A57EFFFB0FFB0FCDF1535C4F34BD5" box="[858,924,1641,1665]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
There are 
<specimenCount id="9D4BFD0FFFB0FFB0FB9E1535C3D54BD5" box="[1051,1210,1641,1665]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="generic">six specimens</specimenCount>
labelled as cotypes from Ankertell, H.W. Brown in (
<collectionCode id="ED5CAE43FFB0FFB0FD8E15D1C50D4BF1" box="[523,610,1677,1701]" country="South Africa" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/ymbs-hrkx" name="Albany Museum" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">AMSA</collectionCode>
), (
<collectionCode id="ED5CAE43FFB0FFB0FDF815D1C5BC4BF1" box="[637,723,1677,1701]" country="Australia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34982" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34982" name="South Australia Museum" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="Museum">SAMA</collectionCode>
), (
<collectionCode id="ED5CAE43FFB0FFB0FD6A15D1C4584BF1" box="[751,823,1677,1701]" country="Australia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:32981" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:32981" name="Australian National Insect Collection" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">ANIC</collectionCode>
) and (
<collectionCode id="ED5CAE43FFB0FFB0FCFA15D1C48F4BF1" box="[895,992,1677,1701]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">MVMA</collectionCode>
). The specimens from (
<collectionCode id="ED5CAE43FFB0FFB0FB6F15D1C2514BF1" box="[1258,1342,1677,1701]" country="Australia" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34982" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34982" name="South Australia Museum" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" type="Museum">SAMA</collectionCode>
) are not 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D05FFB0FFB0FF1215EEC6074B9D" box="[151,360,1713,1737]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="septemplagiata">
<emphasis id="B939EA94FFB0FFB0FF1215EEC6074B9D" box="[151,360,1713,1737]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">M. septemplagiata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but are specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4D4D05FFB0FFB0FDE415EEC5B44B9D" authority="Levey, 2012" authorityName="Levey" authorityYear="2012" box="[609,731,1713,1737]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Melobasis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brittoni" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis id="B939EA94FFB0FFB0FDE415EEC5B44B9D" box="[609,731,1713,1737]" italics="true" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">M. brittoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B939EA94FFB0FFB0FD6615EDC44C4B9D" bold="true" box="[739,803,1713,1737]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A20A57EFFFB0FFB0FD6615EDC44C4B9D" box="[739,803,1713,1737]" pageId="50" pageNumber="51" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
It is possible that Carter may have had these specimens before him when he did the description and incorrectly reported all the specimens as coming from Cue but it seems more likely that Carter labelled specimens he saw at a later date as cotypes.
</paragraph>
